!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

shell /ʃɛl/

(shelling,shelled,shells) 

1. N-COUNT The shell of a nut or egg is the hard covering which surrounds it. (坚果或蛋的) 壳 

例： They cracked the nuts and removed their shells. 他们打破坚果并剥掉果壳。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Shell is the substance that a shell is made of. 壳料 

例： ...beads made from ostrich egg shell. …鸵鸟蛋壳做成的珠子。 

3. N-COUNT The shell of an animal such as a tortoise, snail, or crab is the hard protective covering that it has around its body or on its back. (动物的) 甲壳 

例： ...the spiral form of a snail shell. …蜗牛壳的螺旋形状。 

4. N-COUNT Shells are hard objects found on beaches. They are usually pink, white, or brown and are the coverings which used to surround small sea creatures. 贝壳 

例： I collect shells and interesting seaside items. 我收集贝壳以及海边有趣的东西。 

5. V-T If you shell nuts, peas, shrimp, or other food, you remove their natural outer covering. 剥…的壳 

例： She shelled and ate a few nuts. 她剥了一些坚果吃。 

6. N-COUNT If someone comes out of their shell , they become more friendly and interested in other people and less quiet, shy, and reserved. 矜持 

例： Her normally shy son had come out of his shell. 她那平时害羞的儿子已经开始活跃起来了。 

7. N-COUNT The shell of a building, boat, car, or other structure is the outside frame of it. 框架 

例： ...the shells of burned buildings. …被烧毁的建筑物的框架。 

8. N-COUNT A shell is a weapon consisting of a metal container filled with explosives that can be fired from a large gun over long distances. 炮弹 

例： Tanks fired shells at the house. 坦克向那座房子发射炮弹。 

9. V-T To shell a place means to fire explosive shells at it. 炮击 

例： The rebels shelled the densely-populated suburbs near the port. 那些叛乱者炮击了港口附近人口稠密的郊区。 

10. shelling N-VAR 炮击 

例： Out on the streets, the shelling continued. 在外面街道上，炮击在继续。

